DDL - Data defnition language (CREATE, ALTER, DROP, TRUNCATE)
    CREATE   - used to create new database, schema and tables
	ALTER    - used to modify existing database objects
	DROP     - used to delete existing database objects completely
	TRUNCATE - used to delete rows from the table without deleting the table
	
DML - Data manipulation language (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE, SELECT)
    INSERT - used to add new records to a table
	UPDATE - modify exisiting records in a table
	DELETE - used to remove records from a table
	SELECT - used to select some or all columns (retrive data)
	
DCL - Data control language (GRANT, REVOKE)
    GRANT  - allow access to a database
	REVOKE - withdraw access to a database (unauthorized access)
	
TCL - Transaction control language (COMMIT, ROLLBACK)
	A transaction is a group of one or more sql statements executed as a unit.
    COMMIT   - save database changes and end transaction
    ROLLBACK - undo changes that are not committed and end transaction